    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="499"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d499">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5312/26</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Portuguese Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Montalvão</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1920</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">His Excellency the Secretary of State</hi>: I have the
                    honor to inform Your Excellency that the Government of the Portuguese Republic
                    very readily agrees to the draft of Arbitration Agreement enclosed in the note
                    of the Department of State of March 24, last.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to forward herewith to Your Excellency the Portuguese text of
                    the said Agreement<note n="3" xml:id="d499fn3">Not printed.</note> while
                    expressing in the name of my Government the great satisfaction given it by the
                    prompt assent of the Government of the United States to an extension of the
                    Convention of 1908.</p>
                <p>In compliance with my instruction, I therefore beg Your Excellency to permit me
                    to suggest that it might be better to use in Article II of the said Agreement
                    the phrase “President of the Portuguese Republic” instead of “President of
                    Portugal”. That is the language used in the Portuguese text, and it is my
                    Government’s confident hope that the American Government will accept it.</p>
                <p>Thanking you in advance for the answer which I shall have to forward to my
                    Government, I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Justino de Montalvão</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
